Title 1: Millard Fillmore Suburban Hospital - A Kaleida Health Facility – Buffalo, NY
Meta Description 1: Millard Fillmore Suburban Hospital is a full service, 265-bed acute care teaching hospital and a subsidiary of Kaleida Health, Western New York's largest healthcare provider. The services offered include: ambulatory surgery; Cardiology; cardiac non-invasive procedures; Emergency Department; GI Lab; Imaging; Interventional Radiology; Laboratory; Obstetrics and Gynecology; Palliative Care; Pulmonary Function Lab; Respiratory Therapy; Urology Suite; Vascular Lab; Women's Services; and surgical services in the specialty areas of Minimally Invasive Robotic Surgery, Hand Surgery, Orthopedics, and Neurosurgery. With 12 state-of-the-art operating suites, Millard Suburban Hospital also has an extremely robust surgical program. The Center for Minimally Invasive and Robotics Surgery performs more than 3,000 surgeries annually.

Meta Description 1: Buffalo General Medical Center is proud to be part of the Kaleida Health system and a major teaching affiliate of the University at Buffalo School of Medicine and Biomedical Sciences. As a 501-bed acute care medical center located on the Buffalo Niagara Medical Campus in downtown Buffalo, NY, we provide access to the latest treatment, technology and expert physicians.
